NA/EU do have gameplans, but we're strategically less sound and, in my experience, less open/interested in developing gameplans.

The amount of good players who try to win by prepping for player habits rather than spend, say, a month perfecting a gameplan is baffling 😭

You can prepare for someone AND get long term improvement!
'Player X uses strategy Y against me, let's understand strategy Y more, understand why it counters me, and then develop a counter strategy!'
Vs what I usually see/get requested; a list of habits to hard punish.

Having that strong strategic baseline will help you get the most out of your piloting skills, which I think the west generally surpasses Japan in.
